// DOM Setup
// Bootstraps a fake browser DOM environment using JSDOM so Mermaid can run in Node/Bun.

This module runs immediately on import and must be imported before mermaid.
It creates a minimal HTML document, assigns its globals (window, document, navigator)
to the Node global scope, and polyfills SVG methods that JSDOM does not implement.

The SVGElement.getBBox polyfill returns a fixed bounding box (100x30) because JSDOM
cannot compute text metrics. SVGGraphicsElement is aliased to SVGElement if absent.

DOMPurify is attached to global so isomorphic-dompurify's auto-initialization takes effect.

Exports the window and document objects for consumers that need direct access.
